The n_TOF neutron time-of-flight facility became operational at CERN in 2001 with the aim of providing new and accurate cross section data for neutron-induced reactions relevant to fundamental and applied nuclear science. Neutrons are produced by spallation reactions induced by 20 GeV/c pulses of 7-8×1012\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
