The principle of operation of the FIC for fission cross section measurements is the recording of the energy deposited in the detector gas by the fission fragments produced in very thin targets. The detector gas is in physical contact with the target in order to reduce the energy lost by the fission fragments before entering the detection volume and to obtain a solid angle coverage very close to 2π\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
