The main advantages of the PPAC setup are its fast time response (anode signal of 9 ns FWHM) and the very low thickness of material present in the neutron beam. This last feature, combined with the low gas pressure, makes the detector essentially insensitive to the large flux of prompt γ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
