In such measurements, setups based on recoil-proton telescopes (RPTs) [166] are used to measure the fluence (or intensity) of a neutron beam impinging on a hydrogenous sample, also called “proton radiator”. The energy of the recoil-proton emitted at a given angle is directly related to the energy En\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
