Data on FFAD are scarce and often discrepant, in particular at high energy, due to the lack of neutron beams with adequate spectral features, as well as of suitable detection systems. The n_TOF facility offered the unique possibility of studying FFAD all the way to 1 GeV with high resolution, provided that a proper detection system was developed. To this end, the geometrical configuration of the position-sensitive parallel plate avalanche counters was suitably modified, by mounting the detectors at an angle of 45∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
